WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.720
Once we've created a workspace in RStudio Cloud, a great next step is to add any co-instructors

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:13.920
and teaching assistants to the space to help us get everything set up.

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:18.200
From within our workspace, we click on the Members tab at the top, where by default we

00:00:18.200 --> 00:00:21.280
see any current members already in the workspace.

00:00:21.280 --> 00:00:26.200
We can also click on Invitations to see the status of any pending invitations that we've

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:27.200
sent.

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:31.320
When we click on the Add Member button, we see a pop-up asking us for the new member's

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:37.040
email address, role, and any additional text we wish to include in the invite.

00:00:37.040 --> 00:00:41.040
One thing we need to think about here is what role we'd like to add our co-instructors

00:00:41.040 --> 00:00:44.320
and teaching assistants as.

00:00:44.320 --> 00:00:48.560
Inviting someone as a moderator allows that person to access all of the projects within

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:53.439
a workspace, whereas if we add them as an administrator, they will also have the ability

00:00:53.439 --> 00:00:57.759
to add and remove students, as well as change the workspace settings.

00:00:57.759 --> 00:01:00.880
Whatever we choose, we aren't locked into that option forever.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:07.040
Let's look here, where I've added myself as a member to our data visualization workspace.

00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:12.540
I can change my role by clicking on the drop-down menu and choosing an updated role for any

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.480
member within the workspace.

00:01:15.480 --> 00:01:20.559
Adding members in this way is great when we want to add workspace members one by one.

00:01:20.559 --> 00:01:24.760
Check out our Inviting Learners video for ways to add multiple members at once.

